name: N.U.T.S. field trip
description: Looking for a physical and mental challenge?  Sign up to visit N.U.T.S. for an obstacle course extravaganza!!  This is an off-site trip to an obstacle course gym; bus to leave at 9:30am and return at 2pm  Permission Form will be sent to your school gmail account; print, sign and return to it room 105 ASAP. Cost $20
supervisor: Marybeth, Gail, Taylor Myllari, Nick Graham

name: Cultural Showcase Planning Session
description: We are planning our second annual Cultural Showcase on Discovery Day!  Students who are interested in celebrating the many cultures that are part of our school community are welcome to help out.  Last year, we showcased traditional dress, foods, and art forms.  International Certificate Program students: this option is a great complement to your certificate components.

name: Cupcake Decorating
description: Release your inner Cake Boss!  In this session you will learn how to create fun and yummy cupcakes using different cake decorating techniques.  Learn somethng new and have some fun decorating!   Cost: $5

name: Mindfulness
description: Life causing you Stress... Feeling like your being overwhelmed?  It\'s time to take control and become EMPOWERED!  This workshop will include a “Sound bath” with Crystal Singing bowls and other instruments to facilitate a deep experience of relaxation.  Expect to lay down, let go, relax as you experience simple yet powerful mindful meditations that you can use daily for your own empowerment.

name: Yoga
description: Looking to relax and find inner peace?  Join Ms. Given for an hour of gentle stretching and yoga. Wear comfortable clothes and bring a water bottle.  Yoga mats are available, but feel free to bring your own.

name: Yoga
description: Looking to relax and find inner peace?  Join Ms. Given for an hour of gentle stretching and yoga. Wear comfortable clothes and bring a water bottle.  Yoga mats are available, but feel free to bring your own.

name: String Art Workshop
description: If you like making art and working with your hands, this workshop is for you! In this workshop you will create a finished artwork using string, wood and nails. You will be creating a silhouette pattern on a stained wood panel using your choice of coloured string. At the end of the workshop, you will be able to take your artwork home to display or hang on your walls! This workshop is for all skill levels.  Cost: $11

name: Climbing Wall
description: Always wanted to try out the Climbing Wall in our small gym?  Now\'s your chance! Mr. Ashton will guide you "through the ropes" as you learn to climb!   Permission form required...check your school email account and return the form to Room 105.

name: Journaling & Bookmaking
description: Make your own traveler\'s journal style inserts! Create a custom agenda using washi tape and brush pens, and the finest paper around; design your own personal travel journal, diary, inspiriation book, artist collage book...the possibilities are endless! If you want to also create your book cover, bring recycled leather or denim from home and we\'ll show you how to put it all together! Cost $7

name: Fire Fighting - Specialty
description: Want to know if you have what it takes to be a Firefighter?  Want to know the secrets of the profession?  Meet Ottawa Fire Fighter Sean Armstrong to get the inside scoop of working at a downtown station specializing in ice and water rescue.

name: Fire Fighting - Specialty
description: Want to know if you have what it takes to be a Firefighter?  Want to know the secrets of the profession?  Meet Ottawa Fire Fighter Sean Armstrong to get the inside scoop of working at a downtown station specializing in ice and water rescue.

name: Inuit Games
description: Inuit need to be strong and agile to live on the land. Come and learn the fun and challenging games that Inuit play to ensure their survival!
presenter: Contact:  Ruth Kadlutsiak (Ottawa Inuit Children\'s Centre

name: Inuit Art Forms
description: Get introduced to Inuit culture with this interactive presentation on Inuit Art Forms! Participants will learn about Traditional Inuit Throatsinging and Drumming and will get a chance to try it too!
presenter: Contact:  Ruth Kadlutsiak (Ottawa Inuit Children\'s Centre

name: Opioid Use in our Community
description: This presentation will focus on the types of drugs that are being used in our community and resources that are available for students who have concerns or questions about drug use. Students will also learn about harm reduction work in their community, and how to reduce the risk of harm for the those who are using.  This session will be hosted by our Rideauwood counsellor.

name: Opioid Use in our Community
description: This presentation will focus on the types of drugs that are being used in our community and resources that are available for students who have concerns or questions about drug use. Students will also learn about harm reduction work in their community, and how to reduce the risk of harm for the those who are using.  This session will be hosted by our Rideauwood counsellor.

name: CHEO Nurse
description: Have you ever wondered what nurses REALLY do?  Come find out if you have what it takes to become a nurse!  Join the discussion with a Registered Nurse from the CHEO Emergency Department.   She will explain the different types of nurses that exist in Ontario and the education related to each one, the various areas that nurses can be employed in and all the fun (and sometimes not so fun) things that nurses do.   And don\'t forget...although nursing may sometimes appear to be a female dominated profession there are some pretty talented nurses that also happen to be men out there!

name: California Rolls
description: If you LOVE California rolls you have to sign up for this session. Learn how to make your own delicious California rolls with Mrs. Gilby and Mrs. Thompson. The perfect healthy snack!  Cost $5.00

name: Reverse Engineer & Security Software
description: What does it mean to be in the Information Security field these days? From vulnerability discovery to malware analysis for devices ranging from mobile phones to autonomous vehicle, there is a wide range of ways you can be part of it. We\'ll talk about some vulnerabilities out in the wild, and even create our own vulnerability as an example.

name: Reverse Engineer & Security Software
description: What does it mean to be in the Information Security field these days? From vulnerability discovery to malware analysis for devices ranging from mobile phones to autonomous vehicle, there is a wide range of ways you can be part of it. name: Interior Designer
description:
We will design your own dream room story boards using visual images, paint samples, fabric swatches.
Come away with a clear idea of what it is like to be an interior designer not on TV! Tap into your creative side while learning about the business of design.

name: Entrepreneurship & Pastry Arts: Gingerbread House Construction
description: Local artist, author and cake decorator extraordinaire, Catherine Beddall will demonstrate the techniques for construction of a gingerbread house. Catherine is a professor of Pastry Arts at Algonquin College, her cake business “Catherine’s Cakery” is a going concern and recently she authored and photographed her first book, The Magic of GINGERBREAD. Come watch a master at work! Learn all about how to start your own business and author your first book. Not to mention some killer gingerbread building techniques!!!

name: Civil Litigation Lawyer
description: Wondering what it takes to become a lawyer?  Join the discussion to discover more about the journey required to pass the Bar exam and start practicing law.  Jacquelynne is a local lawyer specializing in family law.  She will share her experiences and answer questions related to her education path and career in law.

description: Wondering what it takes to become a lawyer?  Join the discussion to discover more about the journey required to pass the Bar exam and start practicing law.  Jacquelynne is a local lawyer specializing in family law.  She will share her experiences and answer questions related to her education path and career in law.

name: Escape Room Field Trip
description: Do you enjoy solving puzzles, finding clues and working with others?  Then join us on a fieldtrip to Locksmith, an escape room situated in Kanata. Our goal will be to work together in order to beat the clock and find the key to escape. Bus will leave at 9:55am and return at 12:45pm. Permission Form will be sent to your school gmail account; print, sign and return to it room 105 ASAP.  Cost $25

name: Carpenters Union Field Trip
description: The  Local Brotherhood of Carpenters and Joiners of America have just opened up a new training facility in Kanata.  Join us for a tour of the new building, an activity in the shop plus a chance to ask questions of a trained carpenter and drywaller.  Pizza lunch included!!  Bus will leave at 9:30am and return at 12:30pm.  Steel toes boots are required and bring along a hard hat if you can.  Permission Form will be sent to your school gmail account; print, sign and return to it room 105 ASAP.

name: Badminton
description: Spend an hour in the gym playing badminton!  Singles or doubles...the choice is yours!  Proper clothing and footwear required.  Bring a water bottle too!

description: Spend an hour in the gym playing badminton!  Singles or doubles...the choice is yours!  Proper clothing and footwear required.  Bring a water bottle too!

name: Basketball
description: Looking to work up a sweat?  Come on out and play some pick-up basketball in the gym!  Proper clothing and footwear required.  Bring a water bottle too!

name: Puppy Love!
description: Love puppies and dogs? Then this session is for you! Listen to the owners of Kortar Kennels talk about their experiences with rescue and therapy dogs. There may even be a dog or two to snuggle with!
presenter: Michael Pinfold & Carol Broadhurst Hannah Christmas

name: Puppy Love!
description: Love puppies and dogs? Then this session is for you! Listen to the owners of Kortar Kennels talk about their experiences with rescue and therapy dogs. There may even be a dog or two to snuggle with!
presenter: Michael Pinfold & Carol Broadhurst Hannah Christmas

name: Policing with the RCMP
description: This is your chance to hear from an active Royal Canadian Mounted Police officer.  Sergeant Evans will share with you the pros and cons of a career with the RCMP, the type of policing candidates they seek out as well as his career experiences in protective policing, tactical policing, organized crime and his current Masters degree program in Terrorism and Public Safety.

name: Policing with the RCMP
description: This is your chance to hear from an active Royal Canadian Mounted Police officer.  Sergeant Evans will share with you the pros and cons of a career with the RCMP, the type of policing candidates they seek out as well as his career experiences in protective policing, tactical policing, organized crime and his current Masters degree program in Terrorism and Public Safety.

name: Women in the Trades Q&A
description: Thinking about a career in the trades and/or making a living using your hands?  This is an opportunity for you to meet some fascinating women working with their hands and following their passions.  Bring your questions.
presenter: Mireille St-Denis: HVAC,  Merideth Kucey: Welder/Jewelry Maker, Farren Medynski:welder

name: Board Games & Snacks
description: Board games and Snacks! Learn to play fun interactive and social board games. A time to relax, meet new people, learn some new games and have a few snacks. Possible games include, Settlers of Catan, Magic the Gathering, Werewolf, and Codenames.

name: Wilderness Rescue
description: Learn more about the exciting job of completing rescues in the wilderness.  Dan is a full time firefighter plus he runs a company called Raven Rescue that teaches technical rescues to a variety of user groups ranging from resource organizations and industry to first responders and Military.

name: Wilderness Rescue
description: Learn more about the exciting job of completing rescues in the wilderness.  Dan is a full time firefighter plus he runs a company called Raven Rescue that teaches technical rescues to a variety of user groups ranging from resource organizations and industry to first responders and Military.

name: Massage Therapist and Physiotherapist
description: West Carleton graduates Kelly Gibbons and Vicky Follett share their expertise as a Massage Therapist and Physiotherapist working to help children through rehabilitation.  Come and learn about the pathway towards these careers!

name: Museum of Nature
description: This trip is open to all students but the focus will be directed at senior science students.  Biodiversity and evolutionary relationships will be the focus of the museum visit.  This is a full day field trip (8am-2:15pm).  Permission Form will be sent to your school gmail account; print, sign and return to it room 105 ASAP.  Cost $19
supervisor: Katrina/Kieran (Lindsay Ott if second bus needed)

name: Photograpy
description: Want to make that photo just a little bit more spectacular? Join this session to learn how to use production tools such as editing software to enhance those memorable moments. Make sure to bring some digital photos with you!

name: Video Production
description: Want to know more about what it takes to make a film? Join this session to learn how to use production tools such as editing software and green screens to capture and enhance those memorable moments.

name: Psychologist
description: Prepare to have fun! Through music and games, you will learn about a day in the life of a Clinical Psychologist. This session will be hosted by Dr. Laura Armstrong who is a child, adolescent, and adult Psychologist as well as an Assistant Professor at Saint Paul University in the School of Counselling, Psychotherapy, and Spirituality. Learn about what therapy for mental health concerns looks like in private practice, opportunities in psychological research, and different educational routes.

name: Psychologist
description: Prepare to have fun! Through music and games, you will learn about a day in the life of a Clinical Psychologist. This session will be hosted by Dr. Laura Armstrong who is a child, adolescent, and adult Psychologist as well as an Assistant Professor at Saint Paul University in the School of Counselling, Psychotherapy, and Spirituality. Learn about what therapy for mental health concerns looks like in private practice, opportunities in psychological research, and different educational routes.

name: Criminal Defence Lawyer
description: Join David Anber, a criminal defence lawyer, as he shares his experiences in the fun, fast-paced and mentally challenging field of law. You will learn how he ended up in his specific job, what a typical day is like as well as hear about the series of challenges both within the court and the business side of being a lawyer.

name: Roofing business & Entrepreneurship
description: Rydel Roofing is a local roofing business.  These local businessmen will share information about being an entrepreneur and the task of running a business.  You\'ll also learn about the roofing industry and the different areas it has within it as well as Rydel College that will be launching in Feb 2018 for skilled trades in the roofing industry.

name: Roofing business & Entrepreneurship
description: Rydel Roofing is a local roofing business.  These local businessmen will share information about being an entrepreneur and the task of running a business.  You\'ll also learn about the roofing industry and the different areas it has within it as well as Rydel College that will be launching in Feb 2018 for skilled trades in the roofing industry.

name: Broadcast Journalism
description: A proud WCSS grad - Catherine Lathem has been a reporter with CTV Ottawa for more than 15-years. During her time as a journalist, she’s covered everything from royal visits and federal politics to crime and the courts. Today she’ll share with you the journey of her career path, and take you inside some of the highs and lows of the job. And you will have the chance to be the reporter… there will be time for you to ask her anything you want to know about the job!

name: Essential Oils
description: When school + life combined feels completely overwhelming, we can use some tools like essential oils to calm our nerves.In this class you will learn the basics of essential oils + how to safely and effectively use them. Then we will make a personal stress less blend for you to take home. Cost: $10

name: Chat  with a Team Canada Athlete
description: Come hear what a day in the life of an athlete is like. The highs and lows of having a full time job representing Team Canada and the lessons learned along the way that can be applied to everyday life.

name: Acadia University
description: Learn about applying to the Atlantic Province universities, the Maple League of Universities which includes St. Fx, Bishop\'s, Mount Allison and Acadia. In addition, learn about programs unique to Acadia.

name: Acadia University
description: Learn about applying to the Atlantic Province universities, the Maple League of Universities which includes St. Fx, Bishop\'s, Mount Allison and Acadia. In addition, learn about programs unique to Acadia.

name: Electrician
description: Considering a career as an electrician?  Choose this session to hear from someone who currently works in the field.  You will learn more about the specifics of the job, possible job options, required training and more.

name: HVAC
description: Interested in a career involving Heating and Air Conditioning?  Select this session to learn more about HVAC jobs, required training and what to expect in the field.

name: Writing Workshop
description: Join Ms. Hauch as she provides some valuable insight on ways you can get on the road to becoming a published author.

name: Latin Ballroom Dancing
description: Looking to learn a new style of dance?  WCSS student Taite Hauch-Krueger will be leading a ballroom dance workshop. You will learn the basic Cha-Cha figures and then a small combination. No partner required. Wear running shoes or dance in your bare feet. Comfortable clothes and a bottle of water is recommended.

name: Transitioning from High School to Post-Secondary
description: This is your opportunity to learn about making the most of your post-secondary school experience. During this workshop, you can ask questions of current post-secondary school students who have attended Queen\'s University, Trent University and Carleton University. We will explore topics such as course selection and planning, student life skills, extra-curricular activities and living in residence.
presenter: Jillian Kerr, Emma MacLean, Melissa Belanger

name: Singing and Songwriting Workshop
description: Calling the songwriter in you! This workshop will take you on a journey through the popular song. Together we will navigate rhyming, points of view, lyrical phrasing, form and much more to give you the tools you need to write a great song! Bring your instruments and your singing voices if you like but you do NOT need any experience to join this workshop. ALL are welcome!!

name: Seeking Empowerment, Inspiration & Motivation
description: Here\'s your chance to be empowered in an hour!  You will learn about the 12 Advanced Life Skills Strategies that will assist you in developing some real life skills to be able to do something meaningful in your life. If you start focusing when you’re young, the chances of you having an amazing future full of fortune will increase greatly. This session will teach you core fundamental concepts that are simply explained to assist you to obey your curiosity, seek truth knowledge and illuminate your future.  This presentation will be interactive, so get ready to have lots of fun while learning how to push yourself up in life!

name: Careers in the Armed Forces
description: Considering a career in the Canadian Armed Forces?   An Armed Forces recruiter will describe opportunities for exciting and rewarding careers in the Canadian Military.  Make an informed decision about your future.

name: Careers in the Armed Forces
description: Considering a career in the Canadian Armed Forces?   An Armed Forces recruiter will describe opportunities for exciting and rewarding careers in the Canadian Military.  Make an informed decision about your future.

name: Dealing with Stress in a Stressful World
description: School and life can be stressful.  Learn some useful tricks for managing your own stress levels.

name: Working with Children with Autism
description: Have you thought of a career working with students with special needs? Learn about the rewarding field of working with children with autism.

name: Community Employment Resource Centre
description: Need advice on how to find a part-time job?  Looking to improve your resume writing skills?  This session will be hosted by the Community Employment Resource Centre and will help you get on track towards your first paycheque!

name: Community Employment Resource Centre
description: Need advice on how to find a part-time job?  Looking to improve your resume writing skills?  This session will be hosted by the Community Employment Resource Centre and will help you get on track towards your first paycheque!

name: Life of a Student Athlete
description: Liam Smedley is a former WCSS grad who is currently a member of the Canadian Senior National Slalom Team in Whitewater Canoeing.   In addition to his athletic career, Liam is currently attending Carleton University.  Liam will share his exciting adventures of world travel  and how he manages to balance his education with his passion for his sport.

name: Holistic Nutritionist
description: Join Amy Longard, a Registered Holistic Nutritionist and professionally trained Natural Food Chef, as she discusses how you can lead a healthier and more balanced life. Through nutritional consultation, cooking, ​coaching, education, and cooking, Amy aspires to help people reach their goals and overcome health challenges.

name: Careers in Engineering
description: If you are looking towards a career in Engineering, this session is for you!  Learn more about potential career options, required programs and how to find a job in a field you love.  This session will be hosted by representatives from Carleton University.

name: Environmental Sampling
description: Learn more about the Canadian Nuclear Safety Commission (CNSC) and its role in the Canadian nuclear world. Hear directly from a current co-op student about her academic experience, what a typical day at work is like, and some of her tasks. Coming from an environmental science background and working with the environmental protection team, our presenter will be shedding light on the sampling trips that are done in her division with CNSC, in which different samples are collected to ensure that the public and environment are protected from nuclear activities. Some sampling kits and tools will be demonstrated.

name: Let\'s talk About Sex!
description: Youth guided talk about sexual health. Have all your questions answered by a Public Health Nurse.
